Religion Needs to Become Modern or to Be Forgotten
In the United States, the Democrat Party has recently nominated Hillary Clinton as its presidential candidate.
If the results of the latest polls prove true in the election itself, America will inaugurate its first president, a woman, in January.
In the previous week, across the ocean, British Prime Minister Theresa May discussed Britain's withdrawal from European rules with German Chancellor Angela Merkel.
