"Facebook" applies to fight ad blockers.
The world's most used social network, Facebook, has broadcast a kind of warning shot, suggesting that blocking advertising banners using special tools is unacceptable and users will also have to watch ads.
The popularity of special advertisers is increasing, but this means that companies whose main source of income is advertising are declining.
Facebook has now revealed that it understands the annoying nature of advertising banners, but users will have to live with them in the same way.
It is true, however, that they will be provided with tools to be able to choose for themselves what type of material is being shown to them, reports the BBC.
"As we provide more and more control to people, we will also start showing ads to those who use ad blocking software", said Facebook ad business vice president Andrew Bosworth.
In other words, users will be able to choose the type of ads they see by selecting brands and industries that they find interesting.
"People don't like to see ads that don't apply to them or interfere with enjoying content", remarked Bosworth.
Ad blocking tools on mobile devices usually do not work, from which Facebook gets the biggest attendance, but their reduction in banner exposure is also worth billions in monetary terms.
According to the BBC, advertising blockers are used by around 200 million people.
It has already been reported that in the previous quarter of the business year, Facebook's revenue from advertising was US$6.2 billion, or €5.55 billion.
It should be said that this is not the first time Facebook has been actively involved in determining what network users see in their news streams.
As one of the last steps, Facebook has just begun to act to remove or at least limit "sound" headlines from news streams, behind which is actually hiding "empty" messages.
