In Estonia, Zika virus antibodies were detected in nine people.
In Estonia, nine people have been tested for Zika virus antibodies, which means that they may have come into contact with the infection, says Estonian public broadcaster ERR.
The information provided by the laboratory shows that this year Zika virus tests were carried out on 121 samples and nine of them were positive.
The first cases of Zika have been reported in Finland and Sweden in countries nearby from Estonia.
According to the Estonian Health Administration, no acute cases of Zika virus infection have been recorded in the country and in the case of flu-like symptoms, people do not have to take the Zika virus test, but they have to approach their family doctor.
We have found IgG (immunoglobulin G class) antibodies that show that the test person is infected with Zika or similar virus at some point.
"This does not mean that the patient has contracted Zika virus", explained Paul Naber, head of the infectious diseases department at the laboratory's Synlab.
The Zika virus is transmitted by mosquitoes of the genus "Aedes".
In Latvia there is a problem with the development of high-quality car procurement, said Ingus Rūtins, Vice President of the Auto Association, in an interview with the BNS agency.
Asked whether problems with dumped prices were apparent in the car sector, Rūtins replied in the affirmative.
Sure.
Car purchases, however, differ from service purchases where prices are easier to manipulate.
In any event, the car has to pay a certain amount in the end, as it has to be purchased from the manufacturer.
However, the problem is and can be classified into two groups.
Either the procurer is incompetent and unable to establish a high-quality procurement, resulting in "buying" without real awareness of it.
"Or very conscious procurement is being built to get something concrete, and there are all sorts of miracles there," said the Vice President of the Auto Association.
He pointed out that at the moment it is popular to talk about moving away from the lowest price offer to the most economically advantageous offer as a criterion for determining the winner of the procurement, but in some society there is still a misconception about these things.
Now it is very popular - let's go from the lowest price to the most economically advantageous offer!
However, the criteria must be established in both cases and, once taken into account and assessed, the decision is nevertheless taken on the basis of the lowest price principle.
In qualitative procurement, the technical criteria should be very precise and market-conform.
Points should not be used to assess anything that can be expressed in monetary terms.
Points should not assess fuel consumption, emissions, service services and similar things.
You have to know the life cycle of the car, the mileage, etc., then you can simply count everything together.
"The question then is only about which of the scenarios the customer himself is interested in?" Rūtins explained.
In turn, the project manager of the Auto Association Pēteris Rubulis noted that problems are related to the fact that often the same person creates purchases for cars, work gloves and food, and these purchases are derived from the same model.
We have also been brought to the consultation for spare parts for procurement samples, which, other than a detailed absurdity, was difficult to call.
"The problem is that the compiler of the procurement very often lacks any understanding of the subject matter of the procurement and demands are simply being copied from somewhere", Rubulis admitted.
Rutins, on the other hand, added that the smaller the structure that announces the procurement, the greater the problems.
"Obviously, this is precisely because of a lack of human resources and expertise", said the Association's vice president.
